    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1977-03-27T05:24:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1977-03-27T05:24:00-05:00" n="16"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d16">
                <head>16. Telegram From the Department of State to the White House<note n="1"
                        type="source" xml:id="d16fn1">Source: Carter Library, National Security
                        Affairs, <persName corresp="#p_BZK_1">Brzezinski</persName> Material, Trip
                        File, Box 41, <persName corresp="#p_VCR_1">Vance</persName>, Europe and
                        Moscow, 3/27/77–4/4/77: Cables and Memos, 3/15–31/77. Secret; Nodis. Printed
                        from a copy that indicates the original was received in the White House
                        Situation Room. <persName corresp="#p_BZK_1">Brzezinski</persName> forwarded
                            <persName corresp="#p_VCR_1">Vance</persName>’s cable to <persName
                            corresp="#p_CJE_1">Carter</persName> under a covering memorandum that
                        read in part, “<persName corresp="#p_BLI_1">Brezhnev</persName>’s phone call
                        a nice &amp; clearly <hi rend="italic">deliberate</hi> gesture.” In a March
                        24 letter, <persName corresp="#p_CJE_1">Carter</persName> provided <persName
                            corresp="#p_VCR_1">Vance</persName> with pre-Moscow meeting
                        instructions. (Ibid.)</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1977-03-27T10:24:00+00:00">March 27, 1977, 1024Z</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>68027. For the President and Dr. <persName corresp="#p_BZK_1"
                        >Brzezinski</persName> only. Following telegram Secto 03009 dated March 27,
                    1977 is repeated to you.</p>
                <p>Quote. Secto 3009. Dept pass White House for the President from the Secretary.
                    Subject: Moscow Reception</p>
                <p>My reception on arrival Moscow was most cordial. <persName corresp="#p_GAA_1"
                        >Gromyko</persName> was warm and gracious, and agreed readily on a
                    businesslike work schedule to begin March 28 with a meeting with <persName
                        corresp="#p_BLI_1">Brezhnev</persName>. On the way into town, <persName
                        corresp="#p_BLI_1">Brezhnev</persName> phoned on the car radio, extended a
                    cordial welcome and sent you and me his best wishes. That is about the sum total
                    of initial impressions, as we get down to business tomorrow.</p>
                <p>
                    <persName corresp="#p_VCR_1">Vance</persName>
                </p>
                <p>Unquote</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_CWM_1">
                            <hi rend="strong">Christopher</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
